Our team is here to provide you with a safe, hassle-free experience! Luxury and exotic cars are our "thing" and we are thrilled to share these beauties with you.

In addition to TURO's rules, terms & conditions, please make sure you have fully understood our guidelines before booking one of our vehicles!

CLEANING/COVID-19: 
We assure you we are doing our part in helping slow the spread of COVID-19. We thoroughly clean all of our vehicles, especially hotspot areas, prior to your rental. By cleaning and disinfecting our vehicles it eliminates any cross contamination. We politely ask that you also take your own safety precautions. *IF CAR IS RECEIVED IN DISORDERLY CONDITION, (dirty floor mats, scuffed seats, bugs on exterior, etc.) A $25+ CLEANING FEE WILL BE ASSESSED TO YOUR ACCOUNT AT OUR DISCRETION.* We highly recommend prepaying for POST-TRIP CLEANING, if you know you will not have time to clean your chosen vehicle at the end of your trip. 

Pro tip: Be careful touching leather surfaces with sunscreen on hands or body parts as this stains the surface and a claim will have to be made.

TOLLS: 
Please message us upon booking if you plan to use the Toll Pass..You are not allowed to use your own toll pass and do not recommend paying cash because the car will be double charged. You are responsible for tolls found during your reservation. We will later ask for reimbursement, via TURO, after tolls have cleared at the end of your rental.

GAS: (FOR ALL VEHICLES OTHER THAN TESLA)
Our vehicles use Premium 93 gasoline. Please return fueled otherwise a TURO $10 fee will also be added onto the charge for the amount of gas missing. We ask you to leave proof of all gas receipts reflecting use of 93 Premium gas inside the vehicle.

WHEELS: 
Please thoroughly check the car for any preexistent damages and document it upon check-in, we do a pretty good job at taking photos of these things but if notice anything please let us know right away. Curb rashes happen all the time, and if this happens to you the wheels can be easily repaired. You are responsible for this and we request reimbursement per wheel at $120 each for the repair.

AIRPORT PARKING:
Due to COVID-19 we participate in contactless drop-offs. If you select the Orlando International Airport for your pick up/drop off location, the car will be parked in Terminal B, if this garage is full we will park at the South Economy lot . We cannot release the exact location until the exact time of your trips beginning. A parking ticket will be left in the vehicle to exit, you are responsible for paying to exit the parking garage.

SMOKING/VAPING: 
There is absolutely NO smoking or vaping allowed in our vehicles. TURO charges fee up to $250 and will be assessed if you smoke or vape in our vehicle.
